_id: string;\n  client_name: string;\n  priority: \"P1\" | \"P2\" | \"P3\";\n  category: string;\n  status: \"INVESTIGATING\" | \"OPEN\" | \"RESOLVED\" | \"IN_PROGRESS\";\n  assignedAgent: string;\n  linkedProjectId?: string;\n  linkedDocId?: string;\n  slaSeconds: number;\n  description: string;\n  createdDate: string;\n}\n```\n\n\n**Initializing Mock Data**\n\nI'm now initializing default document and support ticket data structures in `lib/api-auth.ts`. These default data objects will live in the global scope to persist across hot reloads. I'm adding `DEFAULT_API_MOCK_DOCUMENTS` to capture counts and recent records, with new collections for documents and support tickets, all in a global, in-memory store.\n\n\n**Populating Governance Checks**\n\nI'm now populating the governance checks within the mock document data. I've enriched the `governanceChecks` array for each document with several checks, like ISO-27001, Zero-Trust TLS, and others. I'm focusing on ensuring these mock governance checks are meaningful and representative of real-world scenarios.\n\n\n**Refining Ticket Data**\n\nI'm now refining the mock support ticket data, focusing on details like linked project IDs and SLA times. I'm ensuring accuracy across clients. I'm expanding the mock data for more robust testing, including various ticket statuses and assignments, by focusing on simulating realistic scenarios. I'm also ensuring the mock ticket data is correctly associated with client entities.\n\n\n**Validating Mock Data Consistency**\n\nI'm now validating the mock document data's governance checks, and I'm ensuring all tickets have a client association. I've enriched a mock document with several checks, such as ISO-27001, Zero-Trust TLS, etc. My priority right now is ensuring that these mock governance checks are aligned with real-world document specifications.\n\n\n**Implementing Ticket Data**\n\nI'm now implementing the `wireFeed` array to incorporate rich text into ticket details, simulating real-time updates. I'm focusing on crafting a comprehensive mock data structure for tickets, including a new format for detailed communication. The `wireFeed` allows for nuanced updates, and I'm ensuring it aligns with my existing data models.\n\n\n**Integrating Ticket Communication**\n\nI'm now integrating the `wireFeed` array into the support ticket details. This implements communication updates to emulate interactions. I am using a mock wireFeed, which is essential to the ticket's history, for a structured view of the support case.\n\n\n**Initializing Ticket Communications**\n\nI'm now initializing the mock ticket communications within `lib/api-auth.ts`, enriching the ticket data. I've focused on adding `wireFeed` arrays with mock communications to tickets, ensuring more detailed interactions. I'm now making sure all data is robust, and focused on maintaining consistency across all tickets, and their associated client records.\n\n\n**Implementing Global Data Structures**\n\nI'm now incorporating `API_MOCK_DOCUMENTS` and `API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS` as global, in-memory stores in `lib/api-auth.ts`. I've added conditional initialization to prevent re-initialization on hot reloads, ensuring data persistence. This approach streamlines data handling and guarantees a consistent state across sessions.\n\n```typescript\nif (!(global as any)._apiMockDocuments) {\n  (global as any)._apiMockDocuments = { ...DEFAULT_API_MOCK_DOCUMENTS };\n}\nexport const API_MOCK_DOCUMENTS: Record<string, ApiDocumentItem> = (global as any)._apiMockDocuments;\n\nif (!(global as any)._apiMockSupportTickets) {\n  (global as any)._apiMockSupportTickets = { ...DEFAULT_API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS };\n}\nexport const API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS: Record<string, ApiSupportTicket> = (global as any)._apiMockSupportTickets;\n```\n\n\n"}}
